main event: Observers reported seeing three flashing lights over Sandusky, Ohio on November 14, 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1 hour,The objects were initially thought to be extraordinary but were later concluded to be ordinary night lights due to their distance and atmospheric conditions,The conclusion was based on the flashing behavior of the lights, The observers included civilians who reported the sighting to the authorities, The sighting occurred despite the absence of any physical evidence.
sighted object: three flashing lights in the sky
witness description: Civilians who were in the area during the sighting.
